metadata.editComments: Locrian to minor // Bars 2,6: D to D7 // Bars 3,7: Bm to B7 // Bar 4: C#7 to C# // redid melody

after a long time of modding and editting tabs, ive come back to reflect on this tab.  i swapped it to c#minor with an emphasis upon the dominant 7th this tab is playing. the tab is inherently f# dorian, but to put it into a simpler context, i'll keep it in c#minor to emphasize the points I was iterating earlier upon the tonality the lead is cadencing.  the c notes are all the harmonic minor element of the tune, and it's hard to see those when the tab is structured towards and f# style of scale.  in c#minor, it is easier to see.
